<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-05-15T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-05-15T15:00:00-05:00" n="687" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d687">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">550.E1 Russia/4: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Child</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-05-15T16:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">May 15,
                                        1922—4 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>10. Your 53 and 54. We appreciate proposal transmitted by your 54.
                            Entirely inconsistent with French proposal and in this view my #9, May
                            14, 11 p.m. cannot be acted upon. Will telegraph reply to invitation
                            shortly; meanwhile advise at once result of meeting of
                            subcommission.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>